1. docker search

   It searches the images on docker hub
   
   docker search ubuntu
   docker search --filter "is-official=true" --filter "stars=3" ubuntu
   
2. docker run
   
   It checks existence of local image else pulls it from remote registry
   creates a new container
   creates a new top R/W layer for modifications
   creates a N/W interface to connect to N/W(to default if no --net options)
   starts container   
   
   docker run -it ubuntu /bin/bash
   docker run -d ubuntu
   docker run -it --name myubuntu ubuntu
   
3. docker image
   
   This command works on image
   
   docker image ls
   docker image pull
   docker image push
   docker image tag
   docker image history
   docker image load
   docker image save
   docker image tag
   
4. docker ps
    
    Checking the container processes
    
    docker ps
    docker ps -a
    
    
5. docker exec
   
   to go inside container and perfomr checks etc.
   docker exec -it myubun bash
   
6. docker commit
   to create an image from a container
   
7. docker update
   to update the config parameters of a container like cgroups etc.
   
   
                
                

   
   
   
   
